Show your WILDCAT pride! ğŸ¾
As we prepare to welcome students back in just over a week, we'd like to extend this opportunity from Big Athletics for parents and students to order Wildcats masks and gaiters.

To see the products available and get directions on how to place an order, visit: https://www.isd110.org/sites/default/files/files/content/wildcats-masks-and-gaiters.pdf

Waconia Chamber of Commerce
July 1 at 10:02 PM Â·

Teachers in the Workplace Externship - Trades Focus

As part of a grant from the Minnesota Chamber of Commerce Foundation's Business Education Network, teachers partnered with Waconia Chamber of Commerce member businesses. The purpose is to better understand the jobs available and skills required in the trades post graduation and/or for students interested in apprenticeship opportunities.

Waconia Public Schools teachers in the areas of Industrial Technology, Engineering, Chemistry, and Statistics partnered with companies to connect classroom curriculum with the industry.

To learn more about the externship program, please contact the chamber office at 952-442-5812 or email cfenner@destinationwaconia.org.

post_text: Congratulations to Science & Engineering Teacher and Conservation Club Advisor, Michael Jensen, for being awarded the Accomplished Waconia Educator Award for 2020!!
shared_text:
Waconia Education Association
May 19 at 12:19 PM Â·

A heartfelt CONGRATULATIONS to Michael Jensen for being awarded the Accomplished Waconia Educator Award for 2020! One of his nominators had this to say: "Mr. Jensen is one of the most incredible teachers I have ever met. His passion for what he does shows through his teaching style, attitude, and personality every single day. Not only does he do a fabulous job teaching the curriculum, but he ensures that every single student he encounters is taught the life lessons that are needed to be successful. Mr. Jensen has become more than just a teacher for students at Waconia High School, he has become a mentor as well. "

When asked why he became a teacher, Mike said: Having the chance to share life lessons and connect our content to a student's life brings purpose to your life. Having the chance to do this surrounded by a supportive community of educators and families bring joy to your life.

WHS Conservation Club

On Monday, April 20, ISD 110 will participate in a grass-roots effort across the state to share a message of hope and encouragement in the midst of the COVID-19 crisis.

The lights at the WHS stadium, the Bayview field, and the tennis courts will be turned on from 8:30 pm to 10:20 pm (110 minutes). In addition to providing a message of hope and encouragement, we want to celebrate the tremendous support all of our students enjoy from the entire ONE10 community, especially the Class of 2020.

If you'd like to join in, plan to turn on your porch light, yard lights, or any other outdoor lights you may have on Monday night. Here's a chance for all of us to throw a little extra light and love on the Class of 2020! #BeTheLightMN #allinthistogether #WEareONE10

MINNESOTA STATE SCIENCE & ENGINEERING FAIR, held virtually this year. Congratulations to WHS 9th grader, Jack Gootziet, on his accomplishments!

SEAGATE RISING STAR AWARDS
These awards recognize two emerging student scientists whose projects not only exemplify excellence in their category but also demonstrate high degrees of difficulty, thoroughness, complexity, creativity, innovation, and effective communication.

In addition to monetary awards, students will receive trophies and Seagate portable hard drives.

post_text:
Waconia High School is proud to announce its 4 NATIONAL MERIT SCHOLARS! ğŸ™Œ Joshua Hebeisen, Jack Van Nurden, Natalie Meath, Gabriel Willis

Over 1.5 million students across the US take the PSAT test that places them into the National Merit Scholarship competition. Out of these elite students, approximately 50,000 top scorers are identified (about the top 3%). About 34,000 of them are recognized as Commended Scholars and they do not advance in the competition. The remaining students are required to meet a number of other requirements, and if they are successful they are recognized at National Merit Scholars. This group represents the top 1% of an elite group of scholars. For the first time in school history, we have four students who are being recognized. #WildcatPride #WEareONE10

A great day for ICE FISHING on Lake Waconia!ğŸ£
The 5th graders of ISD110 embraced winter today by getting outdoors to participate in the winter activity of ICE FISHING! The students were greeted at In Towne Marina on Lake Waconia by Mr. Trapp, Mr. Jensen, and the WHS Conservation Club students. After a short 5 minute walk on the ice, the students were led to 30 fish houses where they learned to fish with the help of high school students and teachers. Thank you to all the volunteers who donated their time and fish houses today! #WEareONE10

WACONIA PUBLIC SCHOOLS RELEASING 2 HOURS EARLY

This message from Superintendent Pat Devine is for all parents/guardians, staff and students in ISD110.

Waconia Public Schools will close 2-hours early on Friday, January 17. Please note that the release time could be earlier depending on what happens with the weather.

What this means for:

ACTIVITIES - All High School and Middle School Athletics, Activities and Clubs practices/rehearsals & games/events are canceled.

COMMUNITY ED - Kids' Co is open for families contracted for that day. Families will be contacted if Kids' Co will be closing early.
All Community Ed events/practices/classes will be canceled.
No afternoon Preschool or ECFE classes.

post_text:
TAKE DOWN CANCER
Thursday, December 12th, is the Wrestling Program's annual Take Down Cancer Night. 6PM @ WHS.

Money will be raised to give back to the Randy Shaver Take Down Cancer Foundation.

There will be silent auction items to bid on. A bucket will be passed around to collect monetary donations. Take Down Cancer bracelets and calendar magnets also be for sale while supplies last.

WHS will be hosting the Orono Spartans in a duel. This is a battle we all want won. This season we are recognizing and fighting alongside one of our senior wrestler's dads as he continues his battle with cancer.

Thank you for your support.
Nick Hackman
WHS Wrestling Head Coach
#TakeDownCancer #WEareONE10

Each year #WEareONE10 schools have various Veterans Day programs to honor and show thanks to the men and women that have served in the U.S. military. ğŸ‡ºğŸ‡¸

Each school does something unique to express words of thanks and display messages of gratitude in honor of veteran friends and family members. Students are asked, â€œWhat can you do to thank a veteran on Veterans Day?â€ ğŸ™

Today, various program activities included: students reciting the Pledge of Allegiance, a 4th grade class signing the Pledge, members of the WHS band playing the Star Spangled Banner, and veteran friends and relatives joining students for a recognition breakfast.

Thank you veterans, we are thankful for you and your service. #VeteransDay #ThankYou
